data.oai_dc:dc: The lipid content of Orbicella faveolata larvae used to generate Figure 2. Data were taken at the time of photosymbiont infection (T = 0) and two days later (T = 48) for the four treatment groups. Data columns contain lipid quantifications (µg/larva) for the lipid classes WE = wax esters, TAG = triacylglycerol, and PL = phospholipids.
